cli/output/theme.go defines Style{Color string; Bold bool; Dim bool} and Theme{Name string; MarkerID, SpecID, Filepath, LineNumber, Hash, StatusOK, StatusWarn, StatusError, SectionHeader, Command, Hint, DiffAdd, DiffRemove, DiffHunk, CodeComment, CodeString, CodeKeyword, CodeNumber Style}. Style.Apply(s string) string composes the ANSI SGR sequence: codes are collected in order — dim ("2"), bold ("1"), Color (raw SGR parameter) — joined by semicolons, wrapped as \x1b[CODESm + s + \x1b[0m. Zero-value Style (all fields empty/false) returns s unchanged — no escape codes emitted. Color accepts basic ("31"), bright ("91"), 256-color ("38;5;37"), and true color ("38;2;R;G;B") SGR parameters. The CodeXxx elements apply to syntax-highlighted code content (see <ref spec="output.code_colorization">code colorization</ref>). See <ref spec="output.theme_system">theme system</ref>.